<DOC><DOCNO> AP890305-0043 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-05-89 1629EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Italy-Avalanche     03-05 0151</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Italy-Avalanche,0154</SECOND><HEAD>Man Killed In Avalanche</HEAD><DATELINE>AOSTA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Four Austrian tourists were swept away by anavalanche as they were skiing Sunday in northern Italy, and one ofthem was killed, civil defense officials said.   Two skiiers managed to free themselves from the snow and anotherwas rescued by Alpine guides who rushed to the scene in the AostaValley in a helicopter, the officials said.   The Italian news agency ANSA identified the dead man as KarlSchmeikal, 50, of Salzburg, Austria. He was skiing with his wifeHilde and two friends when the avalanche occurred near La Thuile, atan altitude of about 6,000 feet, ANSA said.   Mrs. Schmeikal and the two other members of the group trapped inthe avalanche were not injured, civil defense officials said.   Italian authorities have warned that avalanches may occur becauseof the warm, sunny weather that followed recent heavy snowfalls.</TEXT></DOC>